{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2886", "repo": "rails", "body": "@spastorino unless I'm misunderstanding, it seems like this solution (moving stuff to public) leaves a deficiency for a common use case, when using the asset pipeline defaults (no fallback, digest on).\r\n\r\nIf one wants to reference a compiled asset (e.g. application.css) from a static HTML file (like an email, or like a 500.html page), then there isn't a way to reference that asset without the digest...and the digest isn't known at authoring time.\r\n\r\nThoughts?", "_id": {"$oid": "52383e0abd3543c151010538"}, "issue_id": 2886, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2095677", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2886#issuecomment-2095677", "updated_at": "2011-09-14T17:28:00Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker", "login": "greinacker", "gravatar_id": "1f4455584c55f3c9cfd2d485439603e5", "html_url": "https://github.com/greinacker", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/1f4455584c55f3c9cfd2d485439603e5?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fdd6cd99f4184e944b6afef445f496c04.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 759955, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/greinacker/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2011-09-14T17:28:00Z", "id": 2095677, "owner": "rails"}
